## 9. AUDIT & VERIFICATION

### 9.1 TRUST CODE, NOT AUDITS

**CRITICAL**: Audit reports may be outdated. Only trust actual code behavior.

### 9.2 Audit Commands

```bash
# Quick audit (3 layers, fast for development)
bun run audit

# Full audit (11 layers, comprehensive for CI)
bun run audit:ci

# Specific layers
bun run audit --layer=03    # TypeScript
bun run audit --layer=04    # Design tokens
```

### 9.3 When to Run

- **Before starting**: Establish baseline
- **While developing**: Continuous verification
- **Before committing**: MUST pass full audit
- **After completing**: Generate completion report

### 9.4 Pre-Commit Checklist

- [ ] No hardcoded colors (hex/rgb in JSX)
- [ ] No inline styles (`style={{}}`)
- [ ] All spacing uses `--spacing-*`
- [ ] All typography uses `--font-size-*`
- [ ] No `any` types
- [ ] Tested in light, dark, and warm modes
- [ ] Full audit passes (`bun run audit:ci`)

